== Chicken ==

Preheat your #oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9. Heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan on high heat. Boil a half-full #kettle.

In a #medium bowl{}, add the @British Chicken Breasts{2}, @Peri Peri Seasoning{1%sachet}, @Honey{1%tbsp} and a drizzle of oil. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and toss to coat.

Once hot, lay the chicken into the pan. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry until golden, ~{3-4%minutes}, then turn and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Transfer the chicken to a #baking tray{}, skin-side up. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Rice ==

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @Basmati Rice{150%grams} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Drain in a #sieve, then pop it on top of the pan and allow to steam.

Meanwhile, drain the @Sweetcorn{160%grams}(drained) in a sieve.

== Dressing ==

Heat a large #frying pan on high heat (no oil). Once hot, add the sweetcorn and cook until charred, ~{5-6%minutes}. Adjust the heat if necessary. Stir only twice during this time - you want the sweetcorn to pick up some nice colour. Once cooked, transfer the corn to a #small bowl{} and wipe the pan clean.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve, peel and chop the @Onion{1}(chopped) into small pieces.

In a medium bowl, combine the @Red Wine Vinegar{12%grams} and @Olive Oil{1%tbsp}. Set aside.

== Sauce ==

Pop the (now empty) frying pan back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Add the onion to the pan and stir-fry until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and @Central American Style Spice Mix{1%sachet} and cook for ~{1%minute}. Return the charred corn to the pan.

Pour in the @Chicken Stock Paste{10%grams} and @Water{100%ml}. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer for ~{1-2%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

When the rice is cooked, add to the frying pan along with the @Butter{20%grams}. Stir to combine, then remove from the heat.

Taste the rice and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

When everything's ready, toss the @Wild Rocket{20%grams} in the dressing until evenly coated.

Slice each chicken breast widthways into 2cm thick slices, then share between your plates.

Serve with the charred corn rice on the side. Finish with a drizzle of @Low Fat Natural Yoghurt{75%grams} and the rocket leaves alongside. Enjoy!